    <text>
        <body>
            
            <!-- Begins with the text of the petition. -->
           
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.00980.001.jpg"/>
            
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">        
               
                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">                  
            
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName> <choice><abbr>Esq.</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice> Clerk of the Circuit Court for the <placeName>Dist of Cola.</placeName></salute>
                        <salute>Sir:</salute>
                    </opener>
                    
                    <p>Miss <persName>Amelia Gray</persName> of <placeName>Prince Georges County Maryland</placeName> having claim to the service and labor of the undersigned and having refused or neglected to file in your Office the statement in writing or schedule provided for in the 9th section of the Act of Congress entitled "An act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName> Approved <date when="1862-04-16">April 16th 1862</date>.</p> 
                    <p>You will please file the annexed schedule in pursuance of an act supplementary to the above recited act Approved <date when="1862-07-12">July 12th 1862</date>. The undersigned was not in said <placeName>District</placeName> on the <date when="1862-04-16">16th of April</date> but temporarily absent claiming this <placeName>District</placeName> as her residence and with the consent of her owner.</p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Name</cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Sex</cell>
                            <cell>Height</cell>
                            <cell><choice><abbr>Part</abbr><expan>Particular</expan></choice> Description</cell>
                        </row>                        
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Harriet Liveless</persName></cell>
                            <cell><choice><abbr>abt</abbr><expan>about</expan></choice> 32 years</cell>
                            <cell>Female</cell>
                            <cell>5 Ft 1.&#189; In</cell>
                            <cell>Dark Color</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>George W Liveless</cell>
                            <cell>" 6 "</cell>
                            <cell>Male</cell>
                            <cell></cell>
                            <cell>Dark Color</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    
                    <closer>                        
                        <signed>her mark <persName>Harriet Liveless</persName></signed><lb/>
                        <signed>his mark <persName>George W Liveless</persName></signed><lb/>
                        <signed>Witness<lb/>
                            <persName>ZB Brooke</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.00980.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>paid</ab>
                        <ab><persName>Harriet Liveless</persName></ab>
                        <ab><persName>George W Liveless</persName></ab>
                        <ab>slaves</ab>
                        <ab>Mrs <persName>Amelia Gray</persName></ab>                    
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No 2 folio 104&#8212;</ab>
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-11-11">Nov 11th 1862</date></ab>
                    </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>The commissioners, satisfied on the testimony of <persName>Sarah Ann Keller</persName>, of the truth of the within statement, order the same to be so reported to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</ab>
                        <closer><signed><persName>Wm R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                            Clerk <choice><abbr>Emn</abbr><expan>Emancipation</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>Comn</abbr><expan>Commission</expan></choice></signed>
                        <date when="1862-11-11">Nov. 11, 1862</date>.
                        </closer>
                    </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Certificate given <choice><abbr>Idfd</abbr><expan>Identified</expan></choice> by Miss <persName>S A Keller</persName></ab>
                    </div3>                     
                </div2>
            </div1>
            
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
            
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.00980.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">               
                <dateline><date when="1862-11-11">Nov 11</date>.</dateline>
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Harriet Liveless</persName> and child <persName>George W</persName></ab>
                    <ab>Servant of <persName>Amelia Gray</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">                    
                    <ab><persName>Sarah Ann Keller</persName>. I have known this woman 5 or 6 years living with me. I hired her of <persName><unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">Walter</unclear> Gray</persName> who was agent of <persName>Amelia Gray</persName>. she was given to <persName>Amelia Gray</persName> by <persName><unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">Lester</unclear> Gray</persName></ab>
                    <ab>she went down home voluntarily and alone she sick in the last of February and came back. I have sent &#38; written down to <unclear reason="illegible" cert="medium" resp="#km">owner</unclear> to attend to servant. she has been living with me ever since and no one has made any claim. <persName>Mr Gray</persName> was at my house today but I did not see him. The servant has been at my house backwards &#38; forwards. These servants did belong to my fathers relatives. They all know where the servants <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#jc">work</unclear> I had up to time paid the wages to them but since I have not paid them to any one</ab>
                </div2>                  
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab>Servant says <persName>Mr Gray</persName> brought a bundle for her</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf003v" facs="cww.00980.004.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab><persName>Harriet Liveless</persName> &#38; child</ab>
                    <ab>servant of <persName>Amelia Gray</persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-11-11">Nov 11</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
        </body>
